# 03-FRONTEND - Frontend Development Rules

## Frontend Rules Directory

This directory contains all frontend development rules for Agent Player.

## Files Structure

### Core Frontend Files
- `react-standards.mdc` - React TypeScript standards
- `component-patterns.mdc` - Component design patterns
- `state-management.mdc` - State management rules
- `ui-ux.mdc` - UI/UX requirements
- `testing.mdc` - Frontend testing strategies

## Purpose

Define frontend development standards for:
- React TypeScript development
- Component architecture
- State management
- UI/UX consistency
- Performance optimization

## Rules Coverage
- React component patterns
- TypeScript implementation
- State management
- Responsive design
- Testing requirements

## MANDATORY Frontend Standards
- All components must be TypeScript with strict types
- Functional components with hooks only (no class components)
- Props interfaces required for all components
- CSS modules or styled-components for styling
- Responsive design for all screen sizes
- Accessibility standards (WCAG 2.1) compliance
- Error boundaries for error handling
- Loading states for async operations
- Proper state management (Context API or Redux)
- Component testing with React Testing Library

